The paper also discusses the concept of topological interference management (TIM), which is a subfield of network information theory (cs.NI). The paper uses graph theory to analyze the network topology, which suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) or cs.LG (machine learning).
